theorem Topology.interior_closure_union_closure_compl_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) ∪ closure (Aᶜ) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- The union is obviously contained in `univ`.
    intro x _
    trivial
  ·
    -- To show `univ ⊆` the union, fix an arbitrary point `x`.
    intro x _
    classical
    by_cases hxInt : x ∈ interior (closure A)
    ·
      exact Or.inl hxInt
    ·
      -- We will prove `x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)`.
      by_cases hxCl : x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)
      ·
        exact Or.inr hxCl
      ·
        -- Having excluded both possibilities leads to a contradiction.
        -- From `hxCl : x ∉ closure (Aᶜ)` we deduce `x ∈ interior A`.
        have hIntEq :
            interior A = (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ :=
          Topology.interior_eq_compl_closure_compl (X := X) (A := A)
        have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A := by
          have : x ∉ closure (Aᶜ : Set X) := hxCl
          have : x ∈ (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ := by
            simpa [not_mem] using this
          simpa [hIntEq] using this
        -- But `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`, contradicting `hxInt`.
        have h_subset :
            interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
          Topology.interior_subset_interior_closure (X := X) (A := A)
        exact (hxInt (h_subset hxIntA)).elim

theorem Topology.interior_inter_closure_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ closure A) = interior A := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- The interior of the intersection is contained in `A`, hence in `interior A`.
    have h : (A ∩ closure A) ⊆ A := Set.inter_subset_left
    exact interior_mono h
  ·
    -- `interior A` is an open subset of the intersection, so it lies in its interior.
    have h_subset : interior A ⊆ A ∩ closure A := by
      intro x hx
      have hxA : x ∈ A := interior_subset hx
      have hxCl : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
      exact And.intro hxA hxCl
    exact interior_maximal h_subset isOpen_interior
